      "description": "## How is the Code Organized?\n\nBefore we dive in, let's understand the overall structure.\n\n### Top-level folders:\n\n```\nsih-2025-jharkhand-tourism/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ public/          ‚Üí Static files (favicon, images)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/             ‚Üí All our code lives here!\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .storybook/      ‚Üí Component documentation setup\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .tours/          ‚Üí These tour files!\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ node_modules/    ‚Üí Downloaded libraries (don't edit!)\n```\n\n### The most important folder is `src/`\nThis is where you'll spend 99% of your time. It contains:\n- Components (the building blocks of our UI)\n- Pages (what users see when they visit a URL)\n- Services (code that talks to the server)\n- And more!\n\n**Let's explore each folder...**"
