    {
      "title": "The Index File Pattern",
      "file": "src/components/atoms/Button/index.ts",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "## The index.ts File\n\nThis small file makes importing **much cleaner**.\n\n### Without index.ts:\n```typescript\nimport { Button } from './components/atoms/Button/Button';\nimport { ButtonProps } from './components/atoms/Button/ButtonProps';\n```\n\n### With index.ts:\n```typescript\nimport { Button, ButtonProps } from './components/atoms/Button';\n```\n\n### How it works:\nThe `index.ts` file \"re-exports\" everything from the folder. When you import from a folder, Node.js automatically looks for `index.ts`.\n\n### This pattern is called \"barrel exports\":\n- Cleaner imports\n- Hide internal implementation\n- Easy to change file names later"
