      "description": "## Pages Folder\n\nPages are the **complete screens** users see when they visit a URL.\n\n### Each page:\n- Has its own URL (like `/homestays` or `/login`)\n- Uses a layout as a wrapper\n- Contains organisms, molecules, and atoms\n\n### Our pages:\n\n| Page | URL | What it shows |\n|------|-----|---------------|\n| **Home** | `/` | Landing page with featured content |\n| **Search** | `/search` | Search results with filters |\n| **HomestayDetail** | `/homestays/123` | Details of one homestay |\n| **Booking** | `/booking` | Booking confirmation |\n| **Login** | `/login` | Login form |\n| **Dashboard** | `/dashboard` | Provider dashboard |\n| **NotFound** | `/*` | 404 error page |\n\n### URL to Page mapping:\nThis connection is defined in `App.tsx` using React Router."
