      "description": "## Context Folder\n\nThis folder contains **shared state** that multiple parts of the app need.\n\n### What's \"state\"?\nState is data that can change. Examples:\n- Items in a shopping cart\n- Whether the user is logged in\n- Notification messages\n\n### Why \"context\"?\nNormally, data flows from parent to child components. But what if the Navbar and Footer both need cart info? Context lets us share data without passing it through every component.\n\n### Our contexts:\n\n| Context | What it manages |\n|---------|----------------|\n| **CartContext** | Shopping cart items |\n| **ToastContext** | Notification messages |\n\n### We'll cover this in detail in Tour 04!"
