      "description": "## Types Folder\n\nThis folder defines **what our data looks like** using TypeScript.\n\n### Why define types?\nTypes are like a contract. They say \"a Homestay must have a title, price, and location.\" If something is missing, TypeScript tells you before you run the code!\n\n### Example type:\n```typescript\ninterface Homestay {\n  id: string;         // Unique identifier\n  title: string;      // Name of the homestay\n  price: number;      // Price per night\n  location: string;   // Where it is\n  images: string[];   // List of image URLs\n}\n```\n\n### Benefits:\n- **Autocomplete** - Your editor suggests valid properties\n- **Error prevention** - Can't misspell property names\n- **Documentation** - Types explain what data exists"
