      "line": 1,
      "description": "## Hooks Folder\n\nHooks are **reusable pieces of logic** for React components.\n\n### What's a hook?\nA hook is a special function that adds features to your component. React comes with built-in hooks like:\n- `useState` - Remember data between renders\n- `useEffect` - Do something when data changes\n\n### Custom hooks:\nWe can create our own hooks to reuse common patterns.\n\n### Our hooks:\n\n| Hook | What it does |\n|------|-------------|\n| **useApi** | Fetches data and handles loading/error states |\n\n### Example:\n```typescript\n// Instead of writing fetch logic in every component:\nconst { data, loading, error } = useApi(\n  () => homestaysService.getAll()\n);\n```\n\nThis hook handles loading states, errors, and gives you the data - all in one line!"
